The paper discusses a comparison of two visualization tools and their interaction paradigms, which are related to human-computer interaction (HCI) and information retrieval (IR). The paper also discusses the construction and exploration of data, which is related to databases (DB) and visualization (VIS). Finally, the paper discusses the feeling of control during the visualization construction process, which is related to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HCI, followed by cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.VIS, and cs.CL.
